    "narrative": "LawDog heads into today\u2019s slate with **Jos\u00e9 Ram\u00edrez** anchoring the lineup, boasting an elite 84.88 score. His matchup against Martin P\u00e9rez is the premier play of the day, as the combination of a high-yield SP_xERA (4.78) and his favorable spot in the order maximizes his run-production potential. Following him, the combination of **Lawrence Butler** (74.61) and **Bryson Stott** (69.60) offers high-floor production; **Lawrence Butler** benefits significantly from leading off against Kodai Senga, while **Bryson Stott** is our primary beneficiary of a \"slow delivery\" matchup, with a +4% bump to his SB potential against Pfaadt. While we are waiting on official word for **Cal Raleigh** and **Brendan Donovan**, their current projections remain strong, with **Brendan Donovan** specifically capitalizing on a +14% platoon edge against Lance McCullers Jr.\n\nThe most difficult decision on the bench involved **Taylor Ward** (48.46), who sits just outside the start range due to a challenging matchup against Logan Webb. While the park factors for **Taylor Ward** are highly favorable (+16%), Webb\u2019s elite ability to suppress production significantly eroded the base projection, making him a riskier start than our core infielders. Similarly, **Yainer Diaz** was kept on the bench with a 47.74; even with a favorable matchup, his assumed #8 spot in the order created a negative drag on his overall efficiency. We continue to monitor the weather and lineup statuses for **Cal Raleigh** and **Brendan Donovan**, but at present, our roster is optimized to exploit SP weakness and platoon advantages, particularly with the 13\u201316% boosts afforded to **Jung Hoo Lee**, **Matt Chapman**, and **Luis Arraez** in their respective contests.",
